        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler\n",
        "from sklearn.metrics import mean_squared_error, mean_absolute_error\n",
        "import tensorflow as tf\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.models import Model\n",
        "from tensorflow.keras.layers import Input, LSTM, Dense, Attention"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "SwYBIIgHrsgW"
      },
      "execution_count": 40,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "np.random.seed(42)\n",
        "\n",
        "time_steps = 6000\n",
        "t = np.arange(time_steps)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Two seasonal patterns\n",
        "seasonal1 = np.sin(2 * np.pi * t / 50)\n",
        "seasonal2 = 0.5 * np.sin(2 * np.pi * t / 200)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Trend\n",
        "trend = 0.0005 * t\n",
        "\n",
        "# Noise\n",
        "noise = 0.2 * np.random.randn(time_steps)\n",
        "\n",
        "series = seasonal1 + seasonal2 + trend + noise\n",
        "\n",
        "df = pd.DataFrame({\"value\": series})\n",
        "df.head()\n",
        "plt.figure()\n",
        "plt.plot(series)\n",
        "plt.title(\"Generated Time Series\")\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/",
          "height": 452

        "id": "ArhgU8rnrsz3",

    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "scaler = MinMaxScaler()\n",
        "scaledscaled_data = scaler.fit_transform(df)\n",
        "\n",
        "def create_sequences(data, seq_length=50):\n",
        "    X, y = [], []\n",
        "    for i in range(len(data)-seq_length):\n",
        "        X.append(data[i:i+seq_length])\n",
        "        y.append(data[i+seq_length])\n",
        "    return np.array(X), np.array(y)\n",
        "\n",
        "X, y = create_sequences(scaled_data, 50)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train-Test split\n",
        "split = int(0.8 * len(X))\n",
        "X_train, X_test = X[:split], X[split:]\n",
        "y_train, y_test = y[:split], y[split:]"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ZNUhngbbrs3x"
      },
      "execution_count": 42,
      "outputs": []

      "cell_type": "code",

        "baseline_model = tf.keras.Sequential([\n",

        "\n",
        "baseline_model.compile(optimizer='adam', loss='mse')\n",
        "baseline_model.fit(X_train, y_train, epochs=5, batch_size=32)"

        "inputs = Input(shape=(50,1))\n",
        "lstm_out = LSTM(50, return_sequences=True)(inputs)\n",

        "pred = model.predict(X_test)\n",
